<XMLDocContent PageName="cobalt.logging.LogTargetFile" Title="LogTargetFile class" xmlns="http://www.cobaltrenderer.com/schema/XMLDocSchema.xsd">
  <Paragraph>
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.logging.Welcome">Home</PageRef> ->
    LogTargetFile
  </Paragraph>
  <Section Title="Declaration">
    <Code Language="C++"><![CDATA[class LogTargetFile : public ILogTarget;]]></Code>
  </Section>
  <Section Title="Description">
    <Paragraph>
      The <TypeRef>LogTargetFile</TypeRef> class is an <PageRef PageName="cobalt.logging.ILogTarget">ILogTarget</PageRef> implementation that writes formatted log messages to a file.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
      The target must have a file opened with <PageRef PageName="cobalt.logging.LogTargetFile.OpenLogFile">OpenLogFile</PageRef> before messages are written. If no file is open, messages are ignored.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
      The target flushes after writes whose severity passes the configured flush filter. The default flush filter is <TypeRef>SeverityFilter::WarningOrHigher</TypeRef>.
    </Paragraph>
  </Section>
